      {
        "id": 2819327,
        "name": "Matthew Hemming",
        "username": "Matthew_Hemming",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/dc4da7/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-02-18T22:14:16.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I was well and truly spoiled by some wonderful friends tonight.</p>\n<p>Puligny Montrachet 1er Cru Champ Canet 1985 - Etienne Sauzet<br>\nAn absolutely pristine bottle.  Pale in colour and vibrant in aroma with citrus honey and even some lime characters.  The mid-palate showed a hint of lanolin and some white blossom notes.  Lifted and fresh on the finish this kept imrpoving in the glass and evolved a lemon curd element with air.  92/100</p>\n<p>Chateau Ksara 1960<br>\nServed blind although I did have an idea of its likely identity.  This was a pretty threadbare red with the vestiges of red fruit.  There was a Mediterranean character rather than being Bordeaux-influenced.  Very much fading and on the downslope.  80/100</p>\n<p>Pichon Lalande 1978<br>\nAlso served blind.  This had a deeper colour than the Ksara, with a mature rim, and immediately a greater sense of vibrancy.  Intense bouquet with leather and smoke tones that put me in the mind of Gruaud Larose. Very dry and savoury, with some bloody, ferrous notes.  Quite chunky and dry on the finish, I was thinking a vintage like 1975.  Finished with a hint of VA.  90/100</p>\n<p>Petrus 1982<br>\nAgain, blind.  Much more youthful, graceful and energetic than the previous wines.  Taut even.  The fruit is sweet, but controlled and composed rather than opulent, with truffle tones pointing to Pomerol.  Very pretty red fruit on the palate.  Restrained and self-contained.  I was WAYYYY too young, figuring something like a 2000 Pomerol.  I couldn\u2019t believe how youthful this was but, blind, I wasn\u2019t seduced by the label into rating it more highly.  93/100</p>\n<p>d\u2019Yquem 1959<br>\nA warm bronze / amber colour.  Wonderfully intense and spicy botrytis notes of saffron and dried herbs.  The palate showed great weight and volume but remains refreshing - it has mass without heaviness.  Great creme brulee finish.  96/100</p>\n<p>Brilliant school night wines and then some!</p>\n<p>Matthew</p>",
